<item>
            <title>[MATH-1089] Precision.round() returns different results when provided negative zero as double or float</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1089</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Precision.round(-0.0d, x) = 0.0&lt;br/&gt;
Precision.round(-0.0f, x) = -0.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After discussion on the mailinglist, the result should always be -0.0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
